From: Alexander Vladyko <vladyko@briem.ac.by>

Of course, "red field mouse" [means bank vole, _Clethrionomys glareolus_.
In Russian it is "Ryzhaya (red) polevka (field)". The translation was
incorrect. This species of rodent is the main natural reservoir of Puumala
virus in Tatarstan.
--
Alex Vladyko
